<br>
i have to invalidate any list that puts druids as the easiest or second easiest class to play.  i have to ask this: how come a wizard is harder to play then a druid?  hows that work?<br>
<br>
i notice most people have been putting their own class as hard to play.  hard is fricken ae snaring mobs in fear to pull kite agro after the enchanter has died.  hard is doing shit your class aint designed to do.  thats hard.  when you see a ranger save a fear raid cause of some freak train by acting quick on the kite thats skill cause rangers arnt designed for crowd control.  .  pull 3 level 57s with only druids on crowd control then tell me there aint no damn skill there.   <br>
<br>
i really dislike mez.  its no secret that i think eq would be alot more fun if mez/charm hadnt been invented.  it certainly would demand more skill. <br>
<br>
most all those classes get a vault in difficulty if you start picturing groups without a chanter/bard in it.  btw  why exactly does a necro on crowd control take less skill then an enchanter on crowd control? no answer... of course not cause everyone on this thread didnt realize that in addition to all their other roles a necro sometimes is mezzer via stuns.  how does that complexity not vault them ahead of chanters?  i could go down the list...<br>
<br>
im still shocked by druids the easiest class to play...<br>
<br>
and why for god sakes is a mage way way way harder to play then a shaman.  if its purely cuase mage soloing is harder then shaman soloing then i got to ask why the hell rogues arnt at the top. maybe its cause mages are harder to level to 60 then shamans.  is that really the distinction of hard to play?  bah mages arnt any harder or any easier to play then shamans. really to dispute that i have to get an answer to whats so hard bout playing (not being) a mage.  <br>
<br>
this whole conversation is biased against 3 classes. warriors/monks/rogues.  monks get a vault cause of pulling.  warriors get a vault cause of... what the heck is hard bout being a warrior? oh ya when to hit ae taunt. and rogues get a vault cause of if you fall early in a hard fight it hurts bad for the raid.   the last thing you want to hear 12 seconds into a trak fight that you brought &quot;just enough for&quot; (just enough being dependant on your friends) is the rogue saying &quot;died sorry&quot;   i know cause i did it.   and you know what happened?  we died. we all died....  sure theres nothing hard bout being a rogue. less a raids expecting you to kill the mob and the mob is killing back *stares at the enchanter* the most intense moments for a rogue come when a mob has almost beat your raid and your still alive.  then its a dance.  its a raid saving dance of aggression versus caution.<br>
<br>
