Why are warriors tough to play you ask?<br>
<br>
If you have to ask than I guess you've never been main assist on any ToV/Kael/various_dragon01 raid.  It is the main tank that CAN mean victory or defeat.<br>
<br>
Montyy summed it up fairly well when not doing MA, a warriors role is fairly simple.  Slap on a 2h weapon and help push in the right direction.  HOWEVER, doing MA is not quite so simple.  Aggro management is NOT easy when you WANT mob-x to be hitting you.  It's a lot easier to gain aggro when you don't want it.  Mob positioning is also as vital.  Positioning mob-x so that it doesn't warp into a wall or fall down into lava/water and start summoning random raiders.  Aggro/positioning is everyone's responsibility but guess who hears the brunt of the argument when things go bad....warriors.<br>
<br>
I have played every class out there at some point or another, but not necessarily high enough to know the advantages/disadvantages of each, but enough to know my own limitations of the class and if I could play it well.  Kudos to you out there that CAN play bards, paladins, enchanters and necros.  There is no &quot;list&quot; that can be made up of easiest to difficult classes because it's not the class, it's the person weilding the class.  In a sense, these avatars are merely puppets.  I play a warrior and I play it well.  There is nothing more I can say.  If you don't believe me, come group with me sometime and I'll show you.  I don't claim to know how to play a shaman in the high end game, nor cleric, monk, etc...because that's not the class I've invested my time, energy and thought into for 3 years.<br>
<br>
Just my thoughts on the subject <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
