<br>
If you think botting a cleric and tossing a CH on every few seconds is what clerics do, then I can see why you would disagree.  Just as you would think warriors do nothing more then hit the attack button and they are &quot;good&quot; if they remembered that taunt needs to be trained.  Druids?  Well, sure, druids are the easiest class if you know absolutely nothing about what they actually do.  <br>
<br>
clerics are hardest to play well, because we are always charged with healing everyone, from the ranger and wizard that can't manage aggro to the warrior that is dutifully tanking away (That is when teh pally or SK don't decide they are bored and start taunting).<br>
<br>
Not only are we always charged with the above, but we are in charge of camping out if evac is not an option and the situation calls for it.  We are in charge of deciding that the ranger is going to die and the chanter is going to live.<br>
<br>
When a cleric is really good, they will also participate in crowd control, chanter support (through stuns and roots), mana managment with buffs and heals, and making decisions about the mana efficiency of nukes, heals, stuns or roots.  All against mobs that have beefed up MR and we have no MR debuffers of our own.<br>
<br>
I am not saying that I am the &quot;well played cleric&quot; but I am saying that they are damn hard to play well (although, remarkably easy to bot.  but, you get what you pay for).<br>
<br>
Tarf <br>
